[19:08.74]	Even so as I mine own course have set down:
[19:12.10]	I'll give no blemish to her honour, none.
[19:15.25]CAMILLO	My lord,
[19:16.21]	Go then; and with a countenance as clear
[19:19.37]	As friendship wears at feasts, keep with Bohemia
[19:23.07]	And with your queen. I am his cupbearer:
[19:26.15]	If from me he have wholesome beverage,
[19:29.17]	Account me not your servant.
